# Implementation Review: eden-phase-8c-cutover

## Plan

- Path: `docs/plans/eden-phase-8c-cutover.md`
- Summary: Cut over the in-process dispatch driver. Delete `eden_dispatch.run_experiment` plus the in-process Phase 5/7b end-to-end tests; preserve the lifecycle-reconstruction invariant by extending the existing real-subprocess `pytest.mark.e2e` test; rewrite the malformed-success routing case in `test_store_hardening` to drive `run_orchestrator_iteration` directly through the legitimate `Store` API; update live source/docs to reference the surviving public surface (`run_orchestrator_iteration` plus the scripted workers); preserve historical narration in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/roadmap.md` reworded to past tense.

## Implementation Files

| File | Action | Plan Section |
|---|---|---|
| `reference/packages/eden-dispatch/src/eden_dispatch/driver.py` | Modified | §A — delete `run_experiment`, keep `run_orchestrator_iteration` plus helpers, rewrite module docstring, drop unused `Sequence`/scripted-worker imports |
| `reference/packages/eden-dispatch/src/eden_dispatch/__init__.py` | Modified | §A — remove `run_experiment` from imports + `__all__`, update module docstring |
| `reference/packages/eden-dispatch/tests/test_end_to_end.py` | Deleted | §B — Phase 5/7b in-process e2e tests removed; coverage transferred per §B notes |
| `reference/packages/eden-dispatch/tests/test_orchestrator_iteration.py` | Modified | §C #4 — module docstring no longer references the deleted `run_experiment` symbol |
| `reference/packages/eden-storage/tests/test_store_hardening.py` | Modified | §B — `test_driver_routes_malformed_success_to_validation_error` rewritten as a direct unit test against `run_orchestrator_iteration` plus the legitimate `Store` API; imports narrowed |
| `reference/packages/eden-storage/tests/test_restart_safety.py` | Modified | §B — comment updated to reference the orchestrator service rather than the deleted driver |
| `reference/packages/eden-git/README.md` | Modified | §C #7 — "Integration with eden-dispatch" rewritten to point at the orchestrator service + `run_orchestrator_iteration` |
| `reference/README.md` | Modified | §C #8 — Status section updated to "Through Phase 8c"; `eden-dispatch` row in Packages table reworded |
| `reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_e2e.py` | Modified | §B — extended with `_reconstruct_lifecycle` fold over the post-teardown `SqliteStore.read_range()` to preserve the deleted lifecycle-reconstruction invariant |
| `AGENTS.md` | Modified | §C #9 — added "Phase 8c complete." status block; reworded the Phase 8b and 7b status blocks; updated Commands lead and the §8b service-list table cell |
| `docs/roadmap.md` | Modified | §C #10 — Phase 5b, Phase 7b, Phase 8b complete bullets reworded; Phase 8c bullet promoted to "complete" |
| `docs/plans/eden-phase-8c-cutover.md` | Created | The plan itself |

## Change Summary

- `eden-dispatch.run_experiment` and the in-process Phase 5/7b end-to-end tests are gone. The dispatch package's public surface narrows to `run_orchestrator_iteration` plus the three scripted workers. No deprecation shim — the package is at version `0.0.1` with no external consumers (compatibility policy explicit in the plan).
- The lifecycle-reconstruction invariant from the deleted `test_event_log_reconstructs_full_lifecycle` is preserved as a `_reconstruct_lifecycle` fold inside the existing `pytest.mark.e2e` real-subprocess test in `reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_e2e.py`. The fold runs against `SqliteStore.read_range()` reopened after the orchestrator/worker subprocesses are torn down — the same inspection path the test already used. Three plan tasks → three proposals → three trials → 9 task lifecycle entries; assertion uses 9 (not 7 from the in-process version, which seeded only one plan task).
- The malformed-success → `validation_error` routing case in `test_store_hardening` is rewritten as a direct unit test: ready a proposal, create+claim+submit an implement task with `commit_sha=None`, run `run_orchestrator_iteration`, assert `state == failed` and a `task.failed(reason=validation_error)` event. No scripted workers, no `run_experiment`.
- Verification gates all green locally: ruff clean, pyright 0/0/0, pytest 409 passed, markdownlint clean, JSON Schema metaschema clean. The two unresolved §-refs reported by `spec-xref-check.py` (`spec/v0/README.md` lines 16 against §3.4 and §1.1) are pre-existing on `main` and unrelated to this branch.
- Live-source grep gate: `grep -rn "run_experiment" reference/` returns zero hits. Historical narration in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/roadmap.md` is preserved in past tense by design (per the grep-gate scope discussion in the plan).

## Review Status

Round 0 — awaiting initial review.

## Round 1

Issues addressed:

- **Risk** (`reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_e2e.py:245`): added an explicit `repo.resolve_ref(f"refs/heads/trial/{trial.trial_id}-{slug}") == trial.trial_commit_sha` check inside the per-trial loop, fetching the slug via `store.read_proposal(trial.proposal_id).slug`. This now mirrors the assertion the deleted `test_end_to_end_with_real_integrator` made about the integrator's canonical `trial/*` refs.
- **Nit** (`reference/packages/eden-dispatch/tests/test_orchestrator_iteration.py:4`): rewrote the docstring without the line-leading `+`, replacing the symbolic shorthand with prose ("it finalizes submitted tasks, dispatches downstream work, and promotes successful trials").

Re-ran ruff + pyright + pytest (409 passed, e2e green) + markdownlint after the edits.

